  "texts": [
    "For example, the negative well-being effects of recommender systems used in social media platforms were only discovered through qualitative measurement of the user experience since the quantitative click-rate remained high (Stray et al. 2021).",
    "Furthermore, the inclusion of stakeholders increases the transparency of system development-enhancing procedural fairness, trust and credibility-since stakeholders understand where different metrics and decisions originate from (Stray 2020).",
    "More recently, tech giants such as Meta and Google started to incorporate well-being metrics into their system assessments (Stray 2020; Gaggioli et al. 2017), but there is still much work to be done in terms of selecting such human-centred AI metrics.",
    "Practical example.",
    "While not available as a toolkit as of yet, the IEEE 7000's process (IEEE 7000-2021 2021) could be followed to operationalise value-based metrics."
  ],
